extends org.kuali.rice.kns.bo.KualiCodeBase

This class represents a CashDetailTypeCode, which is used to differentiate records of the same general data structure from one another. For example, a CashReceiptDocument has checks and so does a BursarDepositDocument. To be able to re-use the same table and data structure, we need a field that can act as a flag. Another example involves the fact that a CashReceipt contains a coin record, a currency record, and a change out record (aggregated coin and currency together). Since we use the same tables to represent this, we need an attribute to help differentiate between the bunch especially when they all three must co-exist within the same parent CashReceiptDocument instance.
